# adapters/ — CLI Adapter Registry

## Purpose
Provides a unified interface for spawning and interacting with
different AI CLI tools (Gemini, Claude, OpenCode).

## Files
| File | Type | Transport |
|------|------|-----------|
| `base.js` | JSDoc typedefs | — |
| `gemini.js` | `createGeminiAdapter(config)` | CLI spawn `gemini -p` |
| `claude.js` | `createClaudeAdapter(config)` | CLI spawn `claude -p` |
| `opencode.js` | `createOpencodeAdapter(config)` | HTTP to local OpenCode |
| `pool.js` | `AdapterPool` | acquire/release lifecycle |
| `index.js` | `resolveAdapter(type)` | Factory registry |

## AdapterInstance interface (from base.js)
```
{ type, busy, run({ prompt, cwd, model, timeout }) → RunResult, destroy() }
```

## RunResult
```
{ response: string, exitCode: number|null, errors: string[], totalEvents: number }
```

## Pool usage
```js
let adapter = pool.acquire('gemini');
let result = await adapter.run({ prompt: '...', cwd: '/project' });
pool.release(adapter);
```
